      "id": "b48270b1d08c564724c2f1a752d7cb8c"
    },
    {
      "type": "html",
      "text": "\nAfter a delayed graduation from the Hill School in 1942, Backus attended the University of Virginia, where his father wanted him to major in chemistry. Backus liked the theory, but hated the labs. He spent most of his time at parties, waiting to be drafted. ",
      "id": "e4a1807f7f911e04fac75f69673a755e"
    },
    {
      "type": "html",
